description.narrative: (Ghana): USAID will use fiscal year 2018 funds to partner with the Ghana Health Service (GHS) to create a robust, flexible, and sustainable health care system. Assistance will conduct integrated systems strengthening activities in maternal, newborn, and child health; family planning and reproductive health; malaria; and nutrition interventions. Activities include post-training follow up, clinical coaching and supportive supervision, and expansion of shared learning to improve access to quality health care. Activities will also build the capacity of managers, health workers, and community members to deliver and sustain the use of health services to have the greatest impact on health outcomes. USAID will tailor technical assistance to facilitate country ownership in health systems through expertise in health technologies; advocacy and community mobilization; linkages between the community and health services; and technical assistance in health financing, to build the GHS's financial management capacity to receive direct funding from U.S. Government. USAID's investment in health system strengthening will ensure improved health service delivery and greater health outcomes. .
